commit.message: minmax is working pretty well and the game is playable, but there is still one bug where the utility across the board is equal and the AI picks an invalid move. Also, the algorithm is still super slow and hogs all the memory
ttt game tree now has a working minmax process, but it's really slow. Don't use it
new iris dataset info, perceptron has inertia term (doesn't work yet)
new button for exporting ANN outputs to a .csv
new sample files, load weight button, import weight button
new functions for converting weights from and to CSV files, and some example .csv files
stochastic and batch learning in NN.bp()
evolutionary algorithm functions were moved to their own file
refactoring of neural network initalization and feedforwarding makes code much simpler
GUI.py now has functional view to let you modify the weights of the network, and RulkovNeuron.py has a Rulkov map simulation with demo in matplotlib
